# Conda Intro & Usage

## Intro

### Why anaconda? 
* I would like to be able to manage, clone, share, replenish my development environment. We got npm for js what is the python equivalent?
* Conda is the concatanation of virtualenv and pip. See: http://conda.pydata.org/docs/_downloads/conda-pip-virtualenv-translator.html
* Ultimate goal is to be able to use Docker. We will be using miniconda with docker.

### Install Anaconda following the docs:
* [Install Anaconda Following the Docs](https://docs.continuum.io/anaconda/install)
* !!make sure to export anaconda2 installation folder to your PATH environment variable

[See Miniconda vs Anaconda](### Miniconda vs Anaconda)

## Quick Usage For This Project

    conda env create --file backend.env.yml
    source activate swe573_backend

